                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 850d.00/290.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">President of the International Conference on
                            Spitsbergen</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have the honor to inform your excellency that owing to the regrettable illness
                    of Mr. William Miller Collier and his present <pb facs="1097" n="981"
                        xml:id="pg_981"/> incapacity to perform the duties of Delegate to represent
                    the Government of the United States at the International Conference on
                    Spitzbergen, Mr. Franklin Mott Gunther has been designated additional Technical
                    Delegate to assist the Delegation representing this Government.</p>
                <p>In view of the impossibility of his commission reaching him for some time, I have
                    the honor to request that pending its receipt this announcement be accepted by
                    the Conference as entitling Mr. Gunther to all the rights and privileges of the
                    Conference, with full powers to sign ad referendum the conclusions of the
                    Conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
